City Court of New York — General Term,

Before Fitzsimons, Ch. J., Delehanty and Schuchman, JJ.

October, 1901. Carl A. Schneible, Respondent, v. The Travelers Ins. Co. of Hartford, Defendant; Marcus A. Schnitzer, Appellant. Appeal from an order of the Special Term denying the application of the petitioner appellant to vacate an o der of substituí on. Marcus Schnitzer (Julius Miller, of counsel), for appellant; Joseph Beihilf (Walter J. Rosenstein, of counsel , for respondent.

Order appealed from affirmed, with costs and disbursements of appeal. No opinion.
